title: Mahomes injures ankle, unsure about availability
description: Chiefs QB Patrick Mahomes is unsure about his availability for next week's game after suffering an ankle injury. Andy Reid said it wasn't broken, but "it's sore."
author: Adam Teicher

title: Freeman secures long-term extension with Irish
description: Notre Dame coach Marcus Freeman, who is 30-9 over his three seasons with the Irish, has agreed to a long-term extension that will make him among the highest-paid coaches in the country, a university official confirmed to ESPN on Sunday.
author: Heather Dinich

title: Southampton sack manager Martin after Spurs thrashing
description: Southampton sack manager Russell Martin after a 5-0 thrashing by Tottenham on Sunday leaves the club nine points off Premier League safety.

title: 'I am not good enough' - Guardiola faces daunting and major rebuild
description: Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola faces a mammoth rebuild to revive the fading champions after shock Manchester United loss

title: Southampton sack Martin after Spurs hammering
description: Southampton have sacked manager Russell Martin after their 5-0 hammering by Tottenham on Sunday.

title: Humphries takes nine legs in a row to cruise to win in World Champs opener
description: Reigning champion Luke Humphries got his World Darts Championship defence off to a flying start with a 3-0 win over Thibault Tricole at Alexandra Palace, clinching all nine legs in a row.

title: Josh Allen, Bills win wild shootout with Lions in 90-point barnburner
description: Allen produced four more touchdowns, two by air and two by ground, as he cemented his MVP candidacy and helped end Detroit's 11-game winning streak.
author: Yahoo Sports

title: Eagles beat Steelers to win 10th straight game as Pittsburgh loses T.J. Watt late
description: Philadelphia has now equaled the Lions' record atop the NFC standings.
author: Yahoo Sports
